Package roughcut.media.videoeditor

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ExtractAudioWaveformProgressListener
    This listener interface is used by MediaVideoItem.extractAudioWaveform(roughcut.media.videoeditor.ExtractAudioWaveformProgressListener listener) or AudioTrack.extractAudioWaveform(roughcut.media.videoeditor.ExtractAudioWaveformProgressListener listener)
    MediaItem.GetThumbnailListCallback  
    VideoEditor
    This is the interface implemented by classes which provide video editing functionality.
    VideoEditor.ExportProgressListener
    This listener interface is used by the VideoEditor to emit export status notifications.
    VideoEditor.MediaProcessingProgressListener  
    VideoEditor.PreviewProgressListener
    This listener interface is used by the VideoEditor to emit preview progress notifications.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioTrack
    This class allows to handle an audio track.
    Effect
    This is the super class for all effects.
    EffectColor
    This class allows to apply color effect on a media item.
    EffectKenBurns
    This class represents a Ken Burns effect.
    MediaImageItem
    This class represents an image item on the storyboard.
    MediaItem
    This abstract class describes the base class for any MediaItem.
    MediaProperties
    This class defines all properties of a media file such as supported height, aspect ratio, bitrate for export function.
    MediaVideoItem
    This class represents a video clip item on the storyboard
    Overlay
    This is the super class for all Overlay classes.
    OverlayFrame
    This class is used to overlay an image on top of a media item.
    Transition
    This class is super class for all transitions.
    TransitionAlpha
    This class allows to render an "alpha blending" transition according to a bitmap mask.
    TransitionCrossfade
    This class allows to render a crossfade (dissolve) effect transition between two videos
    TransitionFadeBlack
    This class is used to render a fade to black and fade from black transition between two media items.
    TransitionSliding
    This class allows to create sliding transitions
    VideoEditor.OverlayData
    The overlay data
    VideoEditorFactory
    The VideoEditorFactory class must be used to instantiate VideoEditor objects by creating a new project VideoEditorFactory.create(String) or by loading an existing project VideoEditorFactory.load(String, boolean).
    VideoEditorImpl
    The VideoEditor implementation
    WaveformData
    Class which describes the waveform data of an audio track.
